The article announces several nominations and appointments sent to the Senate. Walter G. Copan is nominated to be the Under Secretary of Commerce for Standards and Technology, Matthew G.T. Martin is nominated to be the United States Attorney for the Middle District of North Carolina, Brian D. Montgomery is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Housing and Urban Development, Glen R. Smith is nominated to be a Member of the Farm Credit Administration Board, Michael B. Stuart is nominated to be the United States Attorney for the Southern District of West Virginia, and James E. Trainor, III is nominated to be a Member of the Federal Election Commission. Additionally, the withdrawal of Daniel Alan Craig's nomination for Deputy Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency is also mentioned.